<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 49pt;text-indent:-49pt;"><b>Item 2.02</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<b>Results of Operations and Financial Condition.</b></div>

<div style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&#xa0;</div>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;text-indent:25pt;">On July 13, 2023, Conagra Brands, Inc. (the &#8220;Company&#8221;) issued a press release which contained information on the Company&#8217;s&#xa0;fourth quarter fiscal&#xa0;2023 financial results. The press release is furnished with this Current Report on Form 8-K as Exhibit 99.1.</div>

<div style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&#xa0;</div>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;text-indent:25pt;">The information furnished pursuant to Item 2.02 of this Current Report on Form 8-K, including Exhibit 99.1, shall not be deemed &#8220;filed&#8221; for purposes of Section 18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;), or otherwise subject to liabilities under that section and shall not be deemed to be incorporated by reference into any document filed under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, or the Exchange Act, whether made before or after the date hereof, regardless of any general incorporation language in such filing.</div>

All comparisons are against the prior-year fiscal period, unless otherwise noted.&nbsp;</p>

			<p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt;">Diluted EPS&nbsp;for fiscal <a data-tblloc="40x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657300438393">2023</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687188025219">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687188038116">22.8%</a>&nbsp;to <a data-tblloc="13x1" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687188055382">$1.42</a>, and adjusted EPS&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687188069625">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687188081444">17.4%</a>&nbsp;to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x1" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687188098469">$2.77</a></p>
			</td>
		</tr>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;"><b><u>CEO Perspective</u></b></p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;">Sean Connolly, president and chief executive officer of Conagra Brands, commented, "Our business delivered strong results in fiscal 2023, as we successfully delivered on our priorities to execute inflation-justified pricing, drive gross margin recovery, and reduce net leverage while investing to maintain the strength of our brands. These efforts, and the continued implementation of our playbook, have our brands well-positioned following the volatility of the past few years. Looking ahead, we anticipate transitioning toward a more normalized operating environment in fiscal 2024 - with easing inflationary pressures and improved supply chain operations - and remain committed to our long-term financial algorithm."</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Total Company&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657299993307">Fourth Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, reported and organic net sales <a data-tblloc="2x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022781659986290835">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049148270">2.2%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049165813">$3.0</a> billion.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">The&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049334186">2.2%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049359561">increase</a>&nbsp;was driven by a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049379536">9.9%</a> improvement in price/mix, which was partially offset by a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049390922">7.7%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660049403285">decrease</a> in volume. Price/mix was driven by the company&#8217;s inflation-driven pricing actions and favorable brand mix.&nbsp;The volume decrease was primarily driven by the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing action<font style="color:#333333;">s and shortages from supply chain disruptions.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left;"><b>Page 2</b></p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Gross profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049499647">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049508835">9.8%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049519257">$783</a> million in the quarter, and adjusted gross profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049823859">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049833892">11.0%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049842458">$803&nbsp;</a>million.&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="55x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657300031982">Fourth quarter</a> gross profit benefited from higher organic net sales and productivity,&nbsp;which more than offset the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions) and unfavorable operating leverage.&nbsp;Gross margin&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049875311">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049885768">183</a> basis points to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="4x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049898776">26.3%</a> in the quarter, and adjusted gross margin&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049914074">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049924191">216</a> basis points to <a data-tblloc="6x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049932524">27.0%</a>.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Selling, general, and administrative expense (SG&amp;A), which includes advertising and promotional expense (A&amp;P),&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049962754">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049972518">45.5%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049981591">$726</a> million in the qu<font style="color:#333333;">arter primarily due to $345 million&nbsp;of brand impairment charges. A</font>djusted SG&amp;A, which excludes A&amp;P,&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660049996959">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660050005761">24.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660050019689">$301</a> million driven b<font style="color:#333333;">y incremental supply chain and technology investments along with&nbsp;increased incentive compensation&nbsp;compared to&nbsp;the prior year quarter.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">A&amp;P for the quarter increased&nbsp;</font><a data-tblloc="10x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F202211141671047348412">49.7%</a><font style="color:#000000;"> to&nbsp;</font><a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660050063043">$69</a><font style="color:#000000;"> million, </font><font style="color:#333333;">driven primarily by increases in modern marketing and customer investments along with wrapping strategic reductions in the prior year period.&nbsp;</font><font style="color:#ff0000;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Net interest expense was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F2022791660050151152">$108</a> million in the quarter. Compared to the prior-year period, net interest expense&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x6" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F2022791660050170543">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F2022791660050179416">12.2%</a> or&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x3" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F2022791660050187647">$12</a> m<font style="color:#333333;">illion, primarily due to a higher weighted average interest rate on outstanding debt.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">The average diluted share count in the quarter was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F2022791660050327584">480</a> million shares.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">In the quarter, net income attributable to Conagra Brands decreased&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F20232241679660641616">76.4%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660050393587">$37</a> million, or&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660050408870">$0.08</a> per diluted share. Adjusted net income attributable to Conagra Brands&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="12x5" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660050427061">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="12x4" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660051208036">5.1%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="12x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660051216702">$299</a> million, or&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F2022791660051225596">$0.62</a> per diluted share. The decrease was&nbsp;driven pri<font style="color:#333333;">marily by the increase in SG&amp;A.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Adjusted EBITDA, which includes equity method investment earnings and pension and postretirement non-service income,&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263861" data-tblv="12" id="led263861F2022791660051274036">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263861" data-tblv="12" id="led263861F2022791660051283076">0.6%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263861" data-tblv="12" id="led263861F2022791660051294195">$594</a> million in the quarter, primarily driven by the increase&nbsp;in adjusted gross profit, offset by higher SG&amp;A and&nbsp;lower pension income.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt; text-indent: 0pt; text-align: left;"><b><u>Total Company Fiscal <a data-tblloc="0x1" data-tblname="263812" data-tblv="12" id="led263812F20235191687188770182">2023</a></u></b><u>&nbsp;</u><b><u>Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt; text-align: left; text-indent: 0pt;">For the full fiscal year, net sales&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x13" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20235191687188849140">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x11" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20235191687188857716">6.4%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x8" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20235191687188871544">$12.3</a> billion. The growth in&nbsp;net sales primarily reflects:</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px;">

		<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
			<td style="width: 18pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width: 18pt;">
			<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&#9679;</p>
			</td>
			<td style="width: auto;">
			<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">a 0.2%&nbsp;decrease&nbsp;from the impact of foreign exchange; and</p>

			</td>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">For the full fiscal year, gross profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189003965">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189014150">15.0%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189024882">$3.3</a> billion and adjusted gross profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189045805">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189055597">16.1%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189063942">$3.3</a> billion as the&nbsp;benefits from higher organic net sales and productivity more than&nbsp;offset&nbsp;the negative impacts from cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions),&nbsp;unfavorable operating leverage, and elevated supply chain operating costs. Gross margin&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="4x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189107756">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189241361">198</a> basis points to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="4x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189181828">26.6%</a> and adjusted gross margin&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189195168">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189249258">226</a> basis points to <a data-tblloc="6x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189231864">27.1%</a>.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">For the full fiscal year, EPS&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189752062">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189760371">22.8%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x1" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189783746">$1.42</a> and adjusted EPS&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x5" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189795029">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x4" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189837635">17.4%</a> to <a data-tblloc="14x1" data-tblname="263849" data-tblv="12" id="led263849F20235191687189851343">$2.77</a>, driven by an increase&nbsp;in&nbsp;adjusted operating profit.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">For the full fiscal year, the Company generated&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263851" data-tblv="12" id="led263851F20235271687885653096">$995</a>&nbsp;million&nbsp;in net cash flows from operating activities and&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263851" data-tblv="12" id="led263851F20235271687885668512">$633</a>&nbsp;million&nbsp;of free cash flow.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Grocery &amp; Snacks Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657299999539">Fourth Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Reported and organic net sales for the Grocery &amp; Snacks segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660051335237">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660051343571">3.6%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F2022791660051355324">$1.2</a> billion in the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, price/mix&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660834514519">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="14x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660834530115">9.1%</a> and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660834548261">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="13x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660834559215">5.5%</a>. Price/mix was driven by favorability in inflation-driven pricing. The volume decrease was primarily driven by the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions and shortages from supply chain disruptions.&nbsp;In the q<font style="color:#333333;">uarter, the company gained share in snacking categories including meat snacks and seeds, and some staples categories including canned pasta&nbsp;and Asian sauces and marinades.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835300580">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835314034">4.5%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="2x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835328717">$156</a> million in the quarter. Adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835351847">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835364347">8.1%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="3x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835378757">$235</a> million&nbsp;as the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions),&nbsp;unfavorable operating leverage, and increased A&amp;P and SG&amp;A more than offset the impacts from&nbsp;higher organic net sales and productivity.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Refrigerated &amp; Frozen Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657300003588">Fourth Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Reported and organic net sales for the Refrigerated &amp; Frozen segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="15x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663088117935">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="15x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663088127664">1.1%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="15x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663088149020">$1.2</a> billion in the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, price mix&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845796630">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845814175">10.4%</a> and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="18x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845828718">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="18x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845838199">11.5%</a>. Price/mix was driven by favorability in inflation-driven pricing. The volume decrease was primarily driven by the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions an<font style="color:#333333;">d&nbsp;shortages from supply chain disruptions due to a third-party supplier shutdown.&nbsp;In the quarter, the company gained share in categories such as frozen sides, multi serve meals, and frozen breakfast sausage.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment decreased to a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="4x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835426566">$43</a> million loss in the quarter as a result of the brand impairment charges outlined above. Adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835439908">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835449131">17.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="5x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835460673">$218</a> million as higher organic net sales and productivity more than offset the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation&nbsp;(including unfavorable commodity positions), unfavorable operating leverage, and increased A&amp;P and SG&amp;A.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>International Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657300008689">Fourth Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Net sales for the International segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663087917870">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663087940696">8.6%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663087957030">$251</a> million in the quarter reflecting:</p>

			<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">a&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="22x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663087990863">0.9%</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="22x7" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20228131663088041710">decrease</a> from the unfavorable impact of foreign exchange; and</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">On an organic net sales basis, price/mix&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="25x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845865062">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="25x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845876742">13.8%</a> and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="24x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845890712">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="24x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845906102">4.3%</a>. Price/mix was driven by inflation-driven pricing. The volume decrease was primarily a result of the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835480363">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835491457">265.0%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="6x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835507368">$21</a> million in the quarter. Adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835520838">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835529870">70.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="7x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835541056">$34</a> million as the benefits from higher organic net sales and&nbsp;productivity&nbsp;were partially&nbsp;offset by the negative impact&nbsp;of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions) and increased A&amp;P and SG&amp;A.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Foodservice Segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657300012778">Fourth Quarter</a> Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Reported and organic net sales for the Foodservice segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="26x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845944550">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="26x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845955102">5.5%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="26x1" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660845972046">$303</a> million in the quarter.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, price/mix increased&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="30x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660846051858">9.3%</a>&nbsp;and volume&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="29x6" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660846017711">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="29x4" data-tblname="263825" data-tblv="12" id="led263825F20227181660846029439">3.8%</a>. Price/mix was driven by&nbsp;inflation-driven pricing. The volume decline was primarily a result of the elasticity impact from inflation-driven pricing actions.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Operating profit for the segment&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835558773">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835567800">46.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="8x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835595723">$32</a> million and adjusted operating profit&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835613611">decreased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835622376">2.3%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20227181660835631690">$28</a> million in the quarter as the benefits of higher organic net sales and productivity were&nbsp;more than offset by the negative impacts of cost of goods sold inflation (including unfavorable commodity positions)&nbsp;and unfavorable operating leverage.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Other&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="53x1" data-tblname="263810" data-tblv="12" id="led263810F2022681657300016886">Fourth Quarter</a> Items</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Corporate expenses&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20228131663089724781">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20228131663089737077">103.5%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20228131663089748565">$108</a> million in the qua<font style="color:#333333;">rter and adjuste</font>d corporate expense&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x6" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20228131663089764461">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x4" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20228131663089773144">50.7%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="11x1" data-tblname="263837" data-tblv="12" id="led263837F20228131663089783848">$82</a> million in the<font style="color:#333333;"> quarter driven by incremental supply chain and technology investments along with increased incentive compensation compared to&nbsp;the prior year quarter.</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Pension and post-retirement non-service income was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F20227181660846326307">$6</a> million in the quarter compared to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="9x2" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F20227181660846339340">$19</a> million of income in the prior-year period.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, equity method investment earnings&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x6" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F20235271687885738215">increased</a>&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x5" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F20235271687885751033">32.8%</a> to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="10x1" data-tblname="263814" data-tblv="12" id="led263814F20227181660846351987">$63</a> million, driven by continued favorable market conditions for the Ardent Mills joint venture, and the venture's effective management through recent volatility in the wheat markets.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, the effective tax rate was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F20227181660846611717">(102.0)%</a> compared to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="19x2" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F20227181660846626747">14.4%</a> in the prior-year period due primarily to a valuation allowance adjustment.&nbsp;The adjusted effective tax rate was&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x1" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F20227181660846645523">24.3%</a> compared to&nbsp;<a data-tblloc="20x2" data-tblname="263848" data-tblv="12" id="led263848F20227181660846654756">22.3%</a> in the prior-year period.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">In the quarter, the company<font style="color:#333333;"> paid a dividend o</font>f $0.33 per share.<font style="color:#333333;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Dividend Update</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Subsequent to quarter-end, the Company's Board of Directors approved an increase of the annual dividend from $1.32 per share to $1.40 per share. The Company's new quarterly dividend payment of $0.35 per share of Conagra common stock will be paid on August 31, 2023 to stockholders of record as of the close of business on July 31, 2023.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Outlook</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><font style="color:#333333;">The company is providing the following guidance for fiscal </font>2024:</p>

<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="width: 100%; text-indent: 0px;">

		<tr style="vertical-align: top;">
			<td style="width: 18pt;">&nbsp;</td>
			<td style="width: 18pt;">
			<p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 10pt;"><font style="color:#333333;">&#9679;</font></p>
			</td>
			<td style="width: auto;">
			<p style="margin: 0pt; text-align: left; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="color:#333333;">Organic net sales growth is expected to be approximately 1% compared to fiscal 2023</font></p>
			</td>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Discussion of Results</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Conagra Brands will host a webcast and conference call at 9:30 a.m. Eastern time today to discuss the results. The live audio webcast and presentation slides will be available on <u>www.conagrabrands.com/investor-relations</u> under Events &amp; Presentations. The conference call may be accessed by dialing 1-877-883-0383 for participants in the U.S. and 1-412-902-6506 for all other participants and using passcode 0327346. Please dial in 10 to 15 minutes prior to the call start time. Following the company's remarks, the conference call will include a question-and-answer session with the investment community. A replay of the webcast will be available on www.conagrabrands.com/investor-relations under Events &amp; Presentations until July 13, 2024.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>About Conagra Brands</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Conagra Brands, Inc. (NYSE: CAG), headquartered in Chicago, is one of North America's leading branded food companies. Guided by an entrepreneurial spirit, Conagra Brands combines a rich heritage of making great food with a sharpened focus on innovation. The company's portfolio is evolving to satisfy people's changing food preferences. Conagra's iconic brands, such as Birds Eye&#174;, Duncan Hines&#174;, Healthy Choice&#174;, Marie&nbsp;Callender's&#174;, Reddi-wip&#174;, and&nbsp;Slim Jim&#174;, as well as emerging brands, including Angie's&#174; BOOMCHICKAPOP&#174;, Duke's&#174;, Earth Balance&#174;, Gardein&#174;, and Frontera&#174;, offer choices for every occasion. For more information, visit <u>www.conagrabrands.com</u>.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Note on Forward-Looking Statements</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt -1pt;">This document contains forward-looking statements within the meaning of the federal securities laws. These forward-looking statements are based on management's current expectations and are subject to uncertainty and changes in circumstances. Readers of this document should understand that these statements are not guarantees of performance or results. Many factors could affect our actual financial results and cause them to vary materially from the expectations contained in the forward-looking statements, including those set forth in this document. These risks, uncertainties, and factors include, among other things: risks associated with general economic and industry conditions, including inflation, rising interest rates, decreased availability of capital, volatility in financial markets, declining consumer spending rates, recessions, decreased energy availability, increased energy costs (including fuel surcharges), supply chain challenges, labor shortages, and geopolitical conflicts (including the ongoing conflict between Russia and Ukraine); negative impacts caused by public health crises; risks related to our ability to deleverage on currently anticipated timelines, and to continue to access capital on acceptable terms or at all; risks related to the Company's competitive environment, cost structure, and related market conditions; risks related to our ability to execute operating and value creation plans and achieve returns on our investments and targeted operating efficiencies from cost-saving initiatives, and to benefit from trade optimization programs; risks related to the availability and prices of commodities and other supply chain resources, including raw materials, packaging, energy, and transportation, including any negative effects caused by changes in levels of inflation and interest rates, weather conditions, health pandemics or outbreaks of disease, actual or threatened hostilities or war, or other geopolitical uncertainty; risks related to the effectiveness of our hedging activities and ability to respond to volatility in commodities; disruptions or inefficiencies in our supply chain and/or operations; risks related to the ultimate impact of, including reputational harm caused by, any product recalls and product liability or labeling litigation, including litigation related to lead-based paint and pigment and cooking spray;&nbsp; risks related to our ability to respond to changing consumer preferences and the success of our innovation and marketing investments; risks associated with actions by our customers, including changes in distribution and purchasing terms; risks related to the seasonality of our business; risks associated with our co-manufacturing arrangements and other third-party service provider dependencies; risks associated with actions of governments and regulatory bodies that affect our businesses, including the ultimate impact of new or revised regulations or interpretations including to address climate change or implement changes to taxes and tariffs; risks related to the Company's ability to execute on its strategies or achieve expectations related to environmental, social, and governance matters, including as a result of evolving legal, regulatory, and other standards, processes, and assumptions, the pace of scientific and technological developments, increased costs, the availability of requisite financing, and changes in carbon pricing or carbon taxes; risks related to a material failure in or breach of our or our vendors' information technology systems and other cybersecurity incidents; risks related to our ability to identify, attract, hire, train, retain and develop qualified personnel; risk of increased pension, labor or people-related expenses; risks and uncertainties associated with intangible assets, including any future goodwill or intangible assets impairment charges; risk relating to our ability to protect our intellectual property rights; risks relating to acquisition, divestiture, joint venture or investment activities; the amount and timing of future dividends, which remain subject to Board approval and depend on market and other conditions; and other risks described in our reports filed from time to time with the Securities and Exchange Commission. We caution readers not to place undue reliance on any forward-looking statements included in this document, which speak only as of the date of this document. We undertake no responsibility to update these statements, except as required by law.</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt -9pt; font-size: 10pt; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; font-size: 10pt; margin: 0pt; text-align: left"><b style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt;"><u>Note on Non-GAAP Financial Measures</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">This document includes certain non-GAAP financial measures, including adjusted EPS, organic net sales, adjusted gross profit, adjusted operating profit, adjusted SG&amp;A, adjusted corporate expenses, adjusted gross margin, adjusted operating margin, adjusted effective tax rate, adjusted net income attributable to Conagra Brands, free cash flow, net debt, net leverage ratio, and adjusted EBITDA. Management considers GAAP financial measures as well as such non-GAAP financial information in its evaluation of the company&#8217;s financial statements and believes these non-GAAP financial measures provide useful supplemental information to assess the company&#8217;s operating performance and financial position. These measures should be viewed in addition to, and not in lieu of, the company&#8217;s diluted earnings per share, operating performance and financial measures as calculated in accordance with GAAP.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Organic net sales excludes, from reported net sales, the impacts of foreign exchange, divested businesses and acquisitions, as well as the impact of any 53<sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">rd</sup> week. All references to changes in volume and price/mix throughout this release are on an organic net sales basis.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">References to adjusted items throughout this release refer to measures computed in accordance with GAAP less the impact of items impacting comparability. Items impacting comparability are income or expenses (and related tax impacts) that management believes have had, or are likely to have, a significant impact on the earnings of the applicable business segment or on the total corporation for the period in which the item is recognized, and are not indicative of the company&#8217;s core operating results. These items thus affect the comparability of underlying results from period to period.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">References to earnings before interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization (EBITDA) refer to net income attributable to Conagra Brands before the impacts of discontinued operations, income tax expense (benefit), interest expense, depreciation, and amortization. References to adjusted EBITDA refer to EBITDA before the impacts of items impacting comparability.</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Hedge gains and losses are generally aggregated, and net amounts are reclassified from unallocated corporate expense to the operating segments when the underlying commodity or foreign currency being hedged is expensed in segment cost of goods sold. The net change in the derivative gains (losses) included in unallocated corporate expense during the period is reflected as a comparability item, Corporate hedging derivate gains (losses).</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><b><u>Note on Forward-Looking&nbsp;Non-GAAP Financial Measures</u></b></p>

<p style="font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;; font-size: 11pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;">Our fiscal 2024&nbsp;guidance includes certain non-GAAP financial measures (organic net sales growth, adjusted operating margin, adjusted EPS, net leverage ratio, and adjusted effective tax rate) that are presented on a forward-looking basis. Historically, the company has calculated these non-GAAP financial measures excluding the impact of certain items such as, but not limited to, foreign exchange, acquisitions, divestitures, restructuring expenses, the extinguishment of debt, hedging gains and losses, impairment charges, legacy legal contingencies, and unusual tax items. Reconciliations of these forward-looking non-GAAP financial measures to the most directly comparable GAAP financial measures are not provided because the company is unable to provide such reconciliations without unreasonable effort, due to the uncertainty and inherent difficulty of predicting the timing and financial impact of such items. For the same reasons, the company is unable to address the probable significance of the unavailable information, which could be material to future results.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">1 </sup>Operating profit is derived from taking Income from continuing operations before income taxes and equity method investment earnings, adding back Interest expense, net and removing Pension and postretirement non-service income.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">2</sup> Advertising and promotion expense (A&amp;P) has been removed from adjusted selling, general and administrative expense because this metric is used in reporting to management, and management believes this adjusted measure provides useful supplemental information to assess the company&#8217;s operating performance.&nbsp; Please note that A&amp;P is not removed from adjusted profit measures.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">3</sup>&nbsp;Includes charges related to consolidated joint ventures. These charges are recorded at 100% for all line items before Net income attributable to Conagra Brands, Inc. Net income attributable to Conagra Brands, Inc. excludes Net income (loss) attributable to noncontrolling interests.</p>

<p style="font-family:'Times New Roman';font-size:10pt;font-variant:normal;margin:0pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">1 </sup>Operating profit is derived from taking Income from continuing operations before income taxes and equity method investment earnings, adding back Interest expense, net and removing Pension and postretirement non-service income.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">2</sup> Advertising and promotion expense (A&amp;P) has been removed from adjusted selling, general and administrative expense because this metric is used in reporting to management, and management believes this adjusted measure provides useful supplemental information to assess the company&#8217;s operating performance.&nbsp; Please note that A&amp;P is not removed from adjusted profit measures.</p>

<p style="font-family: Times New Roman; font-size: 8pt; font-variant: normal; margin: 0pt;"><sup style="vertical-align:top;line-height:120%;">3</sup>&nbsp;Includes charges related to consolidated joint ventures. These charges are recorded at 100% for all line items before Net income attributable to Conagra Brands, Inc. Net income attributable to Conagra Brands, Inc. excludes Net income (loss) attributable to noncontrolling interests.</p>

// Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}

/* Updated 2009-11-04 */
/* v2.2.0.24 */

/* DefRef Styles */
..report table.authRefData{
	background-color: #def;
	border: 2px solid #2F4497;
	font-size: 1em;
	position: absolute;
}

	display: block;
	font-weight: bold;
}

	margin-top: 0px;
}

	text-align: right;
}

	background-color: #2F4497;
}

	height: 150px;
	overflow: auto;
	width: 400px;
}

	font-size: 1em;
}

	color: black;
	text-decoration: none;
}

	background-color: white;
